'''Bari Torre a Mare''' ({{lang-it|Stazione di Bari Torre a Mare}}) is a railway station in the [[Italy|Italian]] town of [[Torre a Mare]], in the [[Province of Bari]], [[Apulia]]. The station lies on the [[Adriatic Railway|Adriatic Railway (Ancona–Lecce)]]. The train services are operated by [[Trenitalia]].

Until 1940 the station was called ''Noicattaro''.

==Train services==
The station is served by the following service(s):

*Regional services (''Treno regionale'') Bari - Monopoli - Brindisi - Lecce

